metadata.metaValue: Caching this instead of the entire source will be much faster/smaller file size

Load a shattered wall model. We output the original instance geo to use with the solver, but instances with many unique meshes slows down the viewport.

So the individual shards are merged (packed) into a single mesh, which is deformed by the result of the simulation. This is what will be displayed in the viewport.

Custom solver example

simulate_bullet is made of mostly general purpose building blocks. These can be used for creating costum solvers with more specific behavior.

bullet_solver_template is a good starting point, it includes the scene setup and stepping, the user just needs to add logic for creating/removing rigid bodies, updating properties etc.
To keep the git repo size down, only the first 120 frames have been cached. Change to Lazy Mode to write the rest
An example of how to set up a custom solver with bullet
